# t/research/memory-prune.test — provisioning leaves in/memory/ EXACTLY the current
# collection, even across turns of the SAME task (feature-memory.md, Fix 4). Task 1's
# workspace persists across a resume; a memory forgotten while task 1 sits open must
# not linger in in/memory/ from turn 1 and be re-handed to the agent on turn 2 (a
# resurrection). käsi prunes the stale note and drops its index line on the resume.

send allow-sender { address kasi@decode.ee }

# Two facts käsi already knows (seeded as the /memory page would).
memory write reply-style   [fixture memory/reply-style.md]
memory write owner-banking [fixture memory/owner-banking.md]

# Task 1 is provisioned BOTH — both notes land in its in/memory/ box on turn 1.
deliver {
    from    kasi@decode.ee
    to      research@kasi.test
    subject "draft"
    body    "draft a reply to the vendor about the overdue invoice"
}
task 1 status is awaiting-agent
task 1 input memory/reply-style.md   matches "*Lead with the answer*"
task 1 input memory/owner-banking.md matches "*Handelsbanken*"

# Turn 1 ends without touching memory; the task returns to the owner (awaiting-user),
# but its workspace — in/memory/owner-banking.md and all — persists.
agent {
    out reply.txt "Drafted the reply."
}
task 1 status is awaiting-user

# While task 1 sits open, the owner forgets owner-banking on the /memory page.
post /memory/owner-banking/forget
memory reply-style matches "*Lead with the answer*"

# A threaded reply reopens task 1 — a RESUME into the SAME workspace. Provisioning
# re-lays memory for turn 2 against the CURRENT collection {reply-style}.
deliver {
    from kasi@decode.ee
    reply-to-last
    body "one more thing — tighten the second paragraph"
}
task 1 status is awaiting-agent

# Turn 2's in/ no longer carries the forgotten note: pruned, not left to resurrect.
# The exact input set is the negative proof — memory/owner-banking.md is gone.
task 1 inputs are {MEMORY.md body.txt memory/reply-style.md}
task 1 input memory/reply-style.md matches "*Lead with the answer*"

# The index was rewritten from the current collection: it lists reply-style and the
# forgotten owner-banking's line does not survive it.
task 1 input MEMORY.md matches {*- [reply-style](memory/reply-style.md) — *}
